{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Freizeit Revue | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = | editor_title = | frequency = Weekly | circulation = 1,011,197 (2010) | category = [[Women's magazine]] | company = [[Hubert Burda Media]] | publisher = Burda Senator Verlag GMBH | founded = {{start date and age|1970}} | firstdate = | country = Germany | based = [[Offenburg]] | language = German | website = [http://www.freizeitrevue.de/ ''Freizeit Revue'] | issn = }}
'''''Freizeit Revue''''' (meaning ''Free Time Review'' in English) is a German language weekly entertainment and women's magazine published in [[Offenburg]], [[Germany]].
==History and profile== ''Freizeit Revue'' was established in 1970.<ref>{{cite web|title=Burda Holding GmbH|url=http://www.referenceforbusiness.com/history2/57/Burda-Holding-GmbH-Co.html|work=Reference for Business|accessdate=25 April 2015}}</ref><ref name="triska">{{cite book|author1=Tristam Carrington-Windo|author2=Katrin Kohl|title=Dictionary of Contemporary Germany|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EbeoAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA167|accessdate=25 April 2015|date=11 April 2013|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-136-59537-0|page=167}}</ref> The magazine is part of [[Hubert Burda Media]].<ref name=bcn>{{cite web|title=Freizeit Revue|url=http://bcn.burda.com/brands/german-magazines/freizeit-revue-the-number-one-for-recreation-and-good-entertainment_aid_1850.html|work=Burda Community Network|accessdate=25 April 2015}}</ref> Burda Senator Verlag GMBH, a subsidiary of the company, publishes the magazine on a weekly basis on Thursdays.<ref name=triska/><ref name=frfact/>
The headquarters of ''Freizeit Revue'' is in Offenburg.<ref name=frfact/> Although men also read the magazine, its major reader group is women over 40.<ref name=frfact>{{cite web|title=Freizeit Revue. Factsheet|url=http://www.publicitas.com/de/belgium/media-solutions/factsheet/mediadata/freizeit-revue/?PARAM1=SOFFO1#.VTup9GTtmko|work=Publicitas|accessdate=25 April 2015}}</ref> The magazine offers interviews with celebrities and articles about health, travel and fashion, among the others.<ref name=bcn/>
During the fourth quarter of 2000 ''Freizeit Revue'' had a circulation of 1,060,297 copies, making it the third best-selling German women's magazine.<ref>{{cite news|author=Fiona Jebb|title=Campaign report on Germany|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/news/37777/|accessdate=25 April 2015|work=Campaign|date=13 April 2001}}</ref> In 2001 it was the sixteenth best-selling women's magazine worldwide with a circulation of 1,060,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top 50 Women’s magazines worldwide (by circulation) 2001 |url=http://www.magazine.org.tw/events/school/report/wmt/Top50Womens.pdf |work=Magazines |accessdate=26 April 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402101746/http://www.magazine.org.tw/events/school/report/wmt/Top50Womens.pdf |archivedate=2 April 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> Its average circulation was 1,028,000 copies in 2003.<ref name=turku>{{cite web|title=European Publishing Monitor|url=http://edz.bib.uni-mannheim.de/daten/edz-du/gda/07/med-ind-germany_en.pdf|work=Turku School of Economics (Media Group)|accessdate=25 April 2015|format=Report|date=March 2007}}</ref> In the fourth quarter of 2006 its circulation was 1,009,800 copies.<ref name=turku/> The total circulation of the magazine was 1,046,000 copies for 2006.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Helmut K Anheier|author2=Yudhishthir Raj Isar|title=Cultures and Globalization: The Cultural Economy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=W0WV1yvMboEC&pg=PA460|accessdate=25 April 2015|date=17 September 2008|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-1-4462-0261-6|page=460}}</ref> The weekly had a circulation of 1,011,197 copies in 2010, making it the second best-selling weekly women magazine after ''[[Bild der Frau]]'' in [[Europe]].<ref>{{cite web|title=World Magazine Trends 2010/2011|url=http://www.revistas-ari.com/attachments/209_WMT_2010_2011_Europe.pdf|work=FIPP|accessdate=4 April 2015|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402165145/http://www.revistas-ari.com/attachments/209_WMT_2010_2011_Europe.pdf|archivedate=2 April 2015}}</ref>
