The '''Landor Theatre''' is a [[Public house|pub]] theatre in [[Clapham]], [[South London]].
Originally the Cage Theatre upon its opening in 1994, the Landor became "Upstairs at the Landor" in 1995 and finally the Landor Theatre in 1998, following a refit of the building.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://s268148492.websitehome.co.uk/landor/about.php|title=About the Landor - a brief history...|accessdate=8 August 2010}}</ref>
In 2010 the Landor staged productions of ''[[Smokey Joe's Cafe]]'', ''[[Closer Than Ever]]'' and ''[[Tomorrow Morning (musical)|Tomorrow Morning]]''.
In 2013 the Landor staged the London premiere of [[title of show]] starring [[Scott Garnham]] as Hunter, Simon Bailey as Jeff, Sarah Galbraith as Susan and Sophia Ragavelas.
