'''Michael Skinner''' (1941{{spaced ndash}} 1998) was an [[Americans|American]] magician known for his [[Micromagic|close-up magic]] work. He was born in [[Rochester, New York]] in 1941; but he spent most of his professional life living and working in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]].<ref>http://www.death-record.com/l/104437109/Michael-B-Skinner</ref> Skinner worked for over 20 years as the magician-in-residence at the [[Golden Nugget Las Vegas|Golden Nugget]], but he also made appearances in other outlets. In particular, he performed twice on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson]]''.<ref name="MagicPedia">[http://www.geniimagazine.com/magicpedia/Michael_Skinner "Michael Skinner"] (2012). MagicPedia. Retrieved 2013-05-03.</ref>

Skinner was known for his large repertoire. He was reported to have once performed 28 consecutive shows without the repetition of a single trick during a full week of bookings at [[the Magic Castle]].<ref>[http://club.magicians.com/video/1409734:Video:4602 "Michael Skinner Magician"] (2012). Club Magician. Retrieved 2012-11-25.</ref>

Skinner studied under magicians Eddie Fechter and [[Dai Vernon]].<ref name="MagicPedia" />

