{{Infobox person | name = Uttam Neupane | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = Surya Kumar Neupane | image = UttamNeupane.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Uttam Neupane at Linewood audio post work | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|02|10}}<!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = [[Rautahat]],[[Nepal]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[Sound mixer]], [[Sound design]]er | yearsactive = 2008 - present
| website = }}
'''Surya Kumar Neupane''' (born 1987), known professionally as '''Uttam Neupane''', is a Nepali [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|sound mixer]] and [[sound design]]er.
==Biography==
Uttam Neupane is a Re-recording sound mixer, Sound designer working within the Nepali Film Industry With a carrier spanning 10 years in film sound design and mixing. He has overseen the audio post production over 70 Nepali Movies. With more than 8 awards, Including National award under his hat. Uttam is the go to guy for film makers who are looking to push the technical limits of the sound in their films and now he is also branching out to the international market as well. He has worked with Benjamin Best on Dirty Games. Uttam has worked on Asian Film Academy Produced Chandra which was screened at the Busan International Film Festival in 2015 and The Sundance Film Festival awarded Dadyaa in 2017.In 2018 He has Sucessfully Mixed Oscar Nominated Eric valli’s Film Beyond The Clouds.
