{{Infobox award | name = Wet Gunpowder Award | image =Wet Gunpowder.jpg | imagesize =150 | caption = | venue = [[Khorramshahr]] | description = | presenter = [[Basij]] | most_nominations = [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] (2) | country = Iran | year = 2013 | website = [http://barotekhis.ir/ barotekhis.ir] }} '''The Wet Gunpowder Award''' ({{lang-fa|جایزه باروت خیس}}) is an [[Iran]]ian symbolic [[award]] that according to organizers, is given to "ridiculous people whose chaffy character is evident to everyone and when this nature of theirs is accompanied with self-belief turns into an indefinite foolishness for them".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.farsnews.com/newstext.aspx?nn=13921226000572|work=[[Fars News Agency]]|script-title=Ashton, Cronberg Receive Symbolic 'Wet Gunpowder' Award|date=March 17, 2014|accessdate=March 17, 2015}}</ref>
The organizers, who have close ties to [[Basij]] and [[Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps]] (The award is unveiled by Basij commander [[Mohammad Reza Naqdi]]), claim award winner is “someone who is against the [[Islamic Revolution]]” and who “against their own wishes, performs a service to the revolution.”<ref name="Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty">{{cite news|first=Golnaz|last=Esfandiari|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/iran-obama-oscars-argo/24946043.html|work=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|script-title= Iran's Basij Awards U.S. First Lady Over Oscars Announcement |date=April 2, 2013|accessdate=March 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Eliana |last=Johnson |url=http://www.nationalreview.com/corner/344375/michelle-obama-receives-iranian-groups-wet-gunpowder-award-eliana-johnson|work=[[National Review]]|script-title= Michelle Obama Receives Iranian Group’s ‘Wet Gunpowder’ Award|date=April 1, 2013|accessdate=March 17, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Al-Monitor"/>
The statue of the award is that of [[brain]] with [[dark glasses]] and [[hearing aids]] with a plaque of the [[Quran]]ic verse: “Unwilling to hear, unwilling to speak, unwilling to see, then, they will not return to the way.”<ref name="Al-Monitor">{{cite news|first= Arash |last=Karami|url=http://iranpulse.al-monitor.com/index.php/2013/04/1698/iran-gives-michelle-obama-wet-gunpowder-award-for-argo/|work=[[Al-Monitor]]|script-title= Michelle Obama Receives Iranian Group’s ‘Wet Gunpowder’ Award|date=April 2, 2013|accessdate=March 17, 2015}}</ref>
In 2015, they awarded a [[parody]] of [[Golden Bear]].<ref name="Mehr News Agency"/>
