{{Infobox person | name = Édgar Ponce | image = | imagesize = 150 px | caption = | birth_name = Édgar Ponce Garcia | birth_date = {{birth date|1977|12|27|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Mexico City]], [[México]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2005|5|5|1977|12|27|df=y}} | death_place = [[Mexico City]], [[México]] | occupation = Actor and dancer }}
'''Édgar Ponce García''' (27 December 1977 &ndash; 5 May 2005) was a [[Mexico|Mexican]] [[actor]] and [[dancer]]. Ponce was a member of the male dance troupe ''[[Solo Para Mujeres|Sólo Para Mujeres]]'' (''For Women Only'') and appeared in a number of [[soap opera]]s (''[[telenovelas]]'') which were popular in both [[Mexico]] and the [[United States]].<ref>[http://www.enelshow.com/news/sandra-ortega-mundo/2010/05/04/255/25674 Profile], enelshow.com; accessed 22 January 2016.</ref>
On 5 May 2005, while filming a commercial with his troupe in [[Mexico City]], an overtaking car slammed into his [[motorcycle]] caravan, sending Ponce flying into the air and injuring three other actors. Ponce was rushed to the hospital but died early the next morning. Police charged the driver with [[manslaughter|involuntary homicide]] and detected alcohol on his breath, but believed he did not intend to kill Ponce. Ponce's co-star [[Alfonso de Nigris|Poncho de Nigris]] accused the man of trying to hit them, stating, "the car didn't hit the brakes or anything".{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
Other controversies ensued due to the troupe riding on the central section of Mexico City [[ring road]] ''(Periférico)'' in violation of a local traffic bylaw requiring motorcycles to use the side lanes, as well as the actions of the producer, Sergio Mayer. Mayer was filming without permission and failed to ask for police assistance; authorities warned he could be charged with a crime.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
